---

Sweet earth, I do not ask for gold,  
Nor stories of the wild winds told,  
Just the gentle sigh of the morning glow  
As I walk where the dreams always flow.  
Among the flowers and the summer's grace,  
I find my solace in nature's embrace.

- Sara Teasdale
